react

Class Try<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • react.Try<T>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Try.Failure, Try.Success

    public abstract class Try<T>
extends Object
    Represents a computation that either provided a result, or failed with an exception. Monadic methods are provided that allow one to map and compose tries in ways that propagate failure. This class is not itself "reactive", but it facilitates a more straightforward interface and implementation for RFuture and RPromise.
